column5: Headed north with my brother for some birds. The weather was less than ideal but wasn't terrible either.
I need feathers, oh yes I do.  Nice birds bud.
Nicely done again!  Thanks for sharing.  Cheers,  Mark
I need feathers, oh yes I do.  Nice birds bud.   Crap, I usually bring some home for the kids but didn't this time. Next time I'll set some aside for you.
Need any duck feathers? I can send you a TON of them if you want them.  S.
Crap, I usually bring some home for the kids but didn't this time. Next time I'll set some aside for you.  Thanks Rob.  Those tail feathers will work great.
Need any duck feathers? I can send you a TON of them if you want them.  S.  Is breast meat  attached ? LOL  Thanks bud. Will pm you.
Nice shooting Rob! Gawd I love the taste of those birds!!!  One of the tastiest meats available IMO

Nice. I haven't hunted grouse in many years.  When my Slovenian grandmother still lived up in Kirkland Lake she would make a fantastic grouse stew from the birds we got.  She would clean them faster than I could ever do it too.   I miss her.  And the stew.  And the rush you get from the first bird of the fall.
Nice birds.  Flushed 5 today, todays snowfall seemed to get them active
I love the ones with the red colouring.. I usually get one or two of them each year..
